question.title: How many measles cases will be reported in the United States in 2026?
question.description: The [latest cases and outbreaks update](https://www.cdc.gov/measles/data-research/?CDC_AAref_Val=https://www.cdc.gov/measles/cases-outbreaks.html) from the CDC reported a total of 1,214 cases reported in 2025 as of June 20, 2025, nearing an annual high over the last two decades of 1,274 cases, which was reached in 2019. As of June 24, 2025, the page states that it is updated every Wednesday, though it had [previously been updated monthly](https://web.archive.org/web/20240124073334/https://www.cdc.gov/measles/cases-outbreaks.html).
question.resolution_criteria: This question will resolve as the number of measles cases reported to the CDC in 2026, according to the [CDC's cases and outbreaks page](https://www.cdc.gov/measles/data-research/?CDC_AAref_Val=https://www.cdc.gov/measles/cases-outbreaks.html). The question will resolve when the first update has been published showing the total number of reported cases through the end of 2026.
question.fine_print:
* If the total number of measles cases reported in 2026 is above 5,000 the question will resolve as above the upper bound.
* If a total for 2026 has not been published before May 1, 2027, this question will be **annulled**.
